-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-10/bp-global-solar-renewables-growth.html
     June 10 (Bloomberg.com) -- From the latest BP energy report,
impressive growth in global renewable energy, up 73 percent year
over year. Most of this is happening in  Europe , and subsidies
there are tapering off to some degree.  The following graph shows solar growth only, which, while
starting from a small base, is still noteworthy.  [via Early Warning]  Click here  to see the story as it appeared on Bloomberg.com.
 